From the manufacturer

Product Description

Your versatile companion for near and far. Designed for ultimate ease, this super soft and packable style transforms our best-selling Uptown into a sleek sneaker. The soft, deconstructed upper pairs with a lightweight, flexible outsole and a high-stability, cushioned footbed, making it the perfect choice for comfort and style on the go. Designed with exclusive alignment technology to balance the whole you. Premium upper materials. Deconstructed to collapse flat. Featuring Vionic's exclusive ultra flex technology. A lightweight flexible outsole that's durable designed to withstand everyday wear. EVA midsole absorbs shock, reducing stress on feet, ankles, and knees. Lightweight, flexible EVA midsole absorbs shock, reducing stress on feet, ankles, and knees. Built-in VIO MOTION Technology footbed featuring contoured arch support, with shock absorbing cushioning, deep heel cup to provide stability and forefoot flexibility. For optimal comfort, wear your new Vionic shoes for a few hours to let your feet adapt. Within 1-2 weeks, you should experience full orthotic comfort and support. 1.1 inch(es) heel height. Imported.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Size: 7.5 WideColor: Cameo Rose SuedeVerified Purchase
    I wore these almost every day on a 10-day vacation in Spain with a lot of walking, and they were wonderful. A little too big without socks, but with socks they fit perfect. I'm a 7.5 in most other shoe brands as well. I'll be ordering these in other colors. I had a hunch I have a planters fasciitis but haven't gone to the podiatrist yet. I definitely do because I had no foot pain in these. So worth the money.
